{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"Mirror how validity is produced, but enforce independence STRUCTURALLY: score novelty in a\nSEPARATE Pass-2 structured sub-call that ALONE receives the prior findings and answers a\nsmall novelty sub-answer set (\"does this finding correspond to a prior finding?\"). The\nexisting verification sub-call (severity attributes + binary/validity) receives NO prior\nfindings, so the `verify.py:64` independence invariant (VERIFIER_RULES[0]) holds by\nconstruction. Pass-1 stays unanchored. Add a `discriminates_novelty` eval scorer + labeled\n(prior-finding, new-finding) carryover/novel pairs on `plan-review-verifier.eval.yaml`; the\nscorer must clear its discrimination bar (the evidence gate) before the Pass-3 drop rule\n(task cc5b) is wired.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Novelty scored in a separate Pass-2 sub-call that alone sees prior findings (`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py`, `src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/verify.py`)\n- [ ] The severity/validity sub-call receives NO prior findings; Pass-1 receives none\n- [ ] Novelty sub-answers are factual (match-prior), not \"should I downrank\"\n- [ ] `discriminates_novelty` scorer + carryover/novel labeled pairs in `src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/plan-review-verifier.eval.yaml` + `eval_scorers.py`\n- [ ] The novelty scorer clears its measured discrimination bar before cc5b activates the drop rule (evidence gate)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782755363034504001,"uuid":"8f159ca9-0ef4-434b-9a04-1ad686f3ba4c"}